04/14/2025,748.2307(8) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,05/13/2025,05/01/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,No,"The purpose of this rule is to prevent harm to children due to the use of behavior management techniques that inflict physical or emotional pain or discomfort.  These prohibited methods of punishment are considered physically, psychologically and/or emotionally abusive.  Using positive methods of discipline and guidance encourage self-esteem, self-control, and self-direction.","MCH has terminated employment of Ms. Flaggs as of today (5/1/2025).  In addition, MCH had a meeting with staff and youth on the Ashcraft Unit to address the concerns to ensure they feel supported and want them to come forward with any issues/concerns immediately regarding mistreatment, abuse/neglect.  MCH management also had a meeting with staff to convey that staff are to step away from youth if there are reasons to believe behaviors are escalating and tempers are not controlled.  To further ensure the safety and well-being of the youth, the Residential Director will increase unannounced walkthroughs of the home. These walkthroughs will help monitor staff behavior and interactions, ensuring adherence to the guidelines discussed."
11/21/2024,748.303(a)(2)(A) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/06/2024,12/09/2024,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,A child in care was taken to the hospital and received medical care. This was not reported within 24 hours. ,"RCCR Inspector Fielteau Conducted an unannounced Inspection at the Methodist Children Home on 12/9/2024 at 1:00 pm.  Three staff members and the Program Administrator were interviewed.

The staff were aware they are required to report serious incidents to licensing within24 hours.  The Program Director stated all staff were re-educated on the procedure of reporting serious incidents to licensing. The Program Director stated staff were informed that all unscheduled visits to the hospital must be reported to licensing.

There were not any further incidents.  No Incident Reports were reviewed.


An email was received on 12/4/24 from Methodist Children's Home administration that states 

""Methodist Childrens Home has taken action to address licensing reporting standards compliance. A reminder was sent out via Microsoft Teams to all case managers and residential supervisors on 12/03/2024 addressing the following:
 MCH is required to report any injury to licensing hotline within 24 hours.
 All case managers and residential supervisors at the Waco Campus acknowledged receiving the reminder."""
